The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Sun Pharmaceutical Industries has allotted 11.39 lakh shares upon conversion of 18,470 foreign currency convertible bonds. The committee of directors has recently allotted the equity shares of Rs 5 each at a premium of Rs 724.30 per share upon conversion of 18,470 FCCBs of $1,000 each, the company has said in a communique to the BSE.

 Minda Industries Ltd has posted a 44.22 per cent rise in net sales to Rs 386.6 crore for 2006-07 from Rs 268.05 crore in the previous year. For the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2007, sales jumped 43.32 per cent to Rs 124.41 crore.

 Endurance Technologies has acquired Italian company Fondalmec S.p.A. Anurag Jain, managing director of the Endurance group, said, This acquisition will help us achieve our goal of being the global leader in the aluminium die casting and machining segment. 

 Reliance Communications has launched two handsets in the FM radio phone segment Classic 261 and Classic 761. The phones are priced at Rs 1,888 and Rs 1,919 respectively.

